Add inserts a brand-new import block before the first declaration when the
file has none at all, AND that first declaration is immediately followed by
an element literal (var xx = <p>...) rather than a plain func/type/const. This
is the shape that regressed: with no import chunk to reuse, `var hello` merges
into the SAME GoWithElements decl as `var xx`, so the synthesized import chunk
must still carry a blank-line separator to the next decl.

-- imports --
goimports
-- add --
fmt
-- input.gsx --
package ui

var hello = "hi"

var xx = <p>{ fmt.Sprintf(hello) }</p>
-- fmt.golden --
package ui

import "fmt"

var hello = "hi"

var xx = <p>{ fmt.Sprintf(hello) }</p>
